---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components'
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About — Zee Marquez"
	description="Zee Marquez — renewable energy specialist combining deep asset engineering with project finance and data science. Solar, wind, IoT, ML, and infrastructure M&A."
>
	<main class="app-container pt-36 pb-4">
		<h1 class="text-6xl pb-2 font-bold">About Me</h1>
	</main>

	<section class="app-container py-8 mb-4">
		<div class="prose prose-neutral prose-lg md:prose-xl dark:prose-invert prose-img:rounded-xl prose-figure:text-center prose-img:mx-auto max-w-3xl">

			<p>
				I'm <strong>Zee Marquez</strong> — a renewable energy specialist who combines
				deep technical expertise in asset engineering with project finance and data science.
				I also like to build cool stuff and learn new things!
			</p>
			<p>
				As a mechanical engineer, I've spent my eraly career years on the asset side of solar and wind projects — structural analysis,
				performance optimisation, CAPEX and OPEX reduction — and I've consistently used
				software, data pipelines, and AI to deliver results that would otherwise require teams
				ten times the size. At GRI I helped reduce wind tower manufacturing costs through FEM-based parametric optimisation. 
				At Vulkano I built an end-to-end IoT and ML platform for solar PV asset monitoring that gives asset managers real-time visibility
				into degradation and maintenance costs — the kind of data that sits at the heart of any
				credible project finance model. I've also worked directly with developers and investors
				on structural due diligence for solar tracker portfolios.
			</p>
			<p>
				Alongside that, I build software and AI products — from knowledge management tools
				to open-source document editors — because engineering complex systems, whether physical
				or digital, is the same discipline applied to different materials.
			</p>

			<!-- Experience -->
			<h2>Experience</h2>

			<h3>Technical Manager — Vulkano Engineering <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Madrid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Nov 2023 – Present</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Structural and performance analysis of solar PV assets for energy developers and asset managers — detailed structural, frequency, and wind load analysis of tracker portfolios to assess design integrity and long-term reliability.</li>
				<li>Led development of <strong>STOWAI</strong>: an IoT-based monitoring platform for utility-scale solar plants that quantifies mechanical degradation, predicts maintenance events, and optimises OPEX — directly informing asset valuation and financing assumptions. Delivered from hardware concept to cloud in under 4 months.</li>
				<li>Forged strategic partnerships with leading Spanish solar developers; secured funding and recognition from Actua UPM, CAM, Wayra, and La Caixa.</li>
				<li>Registered utility model <strong>ES1315071U</strong> for a self-powered mechanical monitoring and predictive maintenance device.</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Structural Engineer — GRI · Gestamp Renewable Industries <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Madrid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Jan 2023 – Oct 2023</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Reduced wind tower manufacturing material costs by <strong>10%</strong> through topology optimisation algorithms embedded in FEM-based parametric tools — translating engineering efficiency directly into CAPEX reduction.</li>
				<li>Migrated legacy FEM/CFD workflows to open-source alternatives, eliminating significant software licensing costs and improving automation across the structural analysis pipeline.</li>
				<li>Applied targeted FEM simulations to resolve critical manufacturing discrepancies, preventing production delays and protecting project timelines.</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Software & Control Engineering Intern — +D (masdediagram) <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· Madrid &nbsp;·&nbsp; Jun 2019 – Jan 2021</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Programmed PLCs and developed software for crash testing and certification machines.</li>
				<li>Designed and assembled industrial automation control systems.</li>
			</ul>

			<!-- Education -->
			<h2>Education</h2>

			<h3>Project Finance and M&amp;A Master — ISBIF <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· 2026</span></h3>
			<p>
				Project finance structuring, infrastructure debt and equity, LBO mechanics, and M&amp;A
				deal execution — with a focus on energy transition and infrastructure assets. A natural
				complement to years of technical work on the asset side of renewable energy projects.
			</p>

			<h3>BSc Mechanical Engineering (English) — Universidad Carlos III de Madrid <span class="font-normal opacity-60 text-base">· 2018 – 2022</span></h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Exchange semesters at Case Western Reserve University and California State University Long Beach (USA) — 4.0 GPA.</li>
				<li>Honors in Physics and Python programming.</li>
				<li>University Moto-Student Team: designed sensorisation and data acquisition systems for racing motorcycles.</li>
			</ul>

			<!-- Skills -->
			<h2>Skills</h2>

			<h3>Renewable Energy &amp; Asset Engineering</h3>
			<p>Finite Element Method (Abaqus, HyperWorks, ANSYS, CALCULIX), CFD (OpenFoam, Fluent), structural analysis (SAP, Revit), CAD (SolidWorks, CATIA, FreeCAD), topology optimisation, fatigue life prediction, wind load analysis, CAPEX/OPEX modelling, Eurocodes, DNV compliance.</p>

			<h3>Data Science, AI &amp; Software</h3>
			<p>Python, C#, C++, MATLAB · AI/ML, predictive maintenance, NLP, deep learning · Backend (FastAPI, Django, GraphQL) · Cloud (AWS, GCP, Azure, Firebase) · Databases (PostgreSQL, InfluxDB, MongoDB) · Dashboards and reporting (Power BI, Grafana, Dash, Streamlit).</p>

			<h3>IoT &amp; Hardware</h3>
			<p>End-to-end IoT architecture, Raspberry Pi, Arduino, PCB design, low-power sensor networks (MQTT, LoRA, OpenThread).</p>

			<h3>Finance &amp; Strategy</h3>
			<p>Project finance, infrastructure M&amp;A, financial modelling · Product lifecycle management, technology roadmapping, Agile, stakeholder communication.</p>

			<!-- Accomplishments -->
			<h2>Accomplishments &amp; Certifications</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Registered utility model <strong>ES1315071U</strong> — self-powered mechanical monitoring and predictive maintenance device.</li>
				<li>Hackathon Datafest 2025 (Santander &amp; Talent Hackers) — large-dataset business challenges using NLP and deep learning.</li>
				<li>Project Akademia — Fundación Bankinter.</li>
				<li>Deep Learning Course — Fundación Universidad Carlos III.</li>
				<li>Master courses in aerodynamics, CFD, and wind resource assessment — TU Delft.</li>
			</ul>

		</div>

		<!-- CTAs -->
		<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-10">
			<a
				class="btn-primary"
				href="/cv/CV Zee Marquez.pdf"
				download
				target="_blank"
			>
				Download CV
				<Icon height={20} name="mdi:arrow-collapse-down" />
			</a>
			<a
				class="btn-secondary"
				href="mailto:zeemarquez@outlook.com"
				target="_blank"
			>
